The course treats the aims, methods and main principles of literary instruction. The structure of literary classes is analysed, as well as the curricula of compulsory and secondary schools. The required reading is handed out in the lectures.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To observe the methods and problems of teaching literature at basic and secondary school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course, the student: - is capable of using didactic principles and methods in pedagogical work; - is capable of managing the different roles of the teacher and problems of professional ethics; - demonstrates  the ability to prepare lessons on literature (settin lesson goals, structure, methods, activities, evaluation time management etc); - is capable of analyzing and interpreting prose-poetry, and drama texts; - has the skills necessary for the treatment of topics collateral to literature (cultural context, integration with other subjects, values education, development of creativity, etc).
